ZH: 这个地区的土地已经变得荒芜了。
EN: The land in this area has become barren.

ZH: 荒芜的山脉看起来非常凄凉。
EN: The barren mountains looked very desolate.

ZH: 这个小村庄因为缺水而变得荒芜。
EN: This small village has become barren due to lack of water.

ZH: 荒芜的土地上漫步，让我感到非常孤独。
EN: Walking on the barren land made me feel very lonely.

ZH: 大旱导致了这个地区变得荒芜。
EN: The severe drought has caused this area to become barren.

ZH: 这片荒芜的土地需要经济支持才能恢复。
EN: This barren land needs economic support in order to recover.

ZH: 荒芜的田地里，只有几颗残留的农作物。
EN: In the barren fields, only a few remaining crops are left.

ZH: 这片荒芜的草原曾经是一片绿洲。
EN: This barren grassland used to be an oasis.

ZH: 荒芜的土地给生态系统造成了严重破坏。
EN: The barren land has caused serious damage to the ecosystem.

ZH: 没有足够的降雨会导致土地变得荒芜。
EN: Insufficient rainfall will cause the land to become barren.

ZH: 这片土地曾经是一片繁华的城市，现在已经变得荒芜。
EN: This land used to be a thriving city, but now it has become barren.

ZH: 荒芜的荒地里传来了野兽的嚎叫。
EN: The barren wasteland echoed with the howls of wild beasts.

ZH: 这个边境城市已经变得荒芜，几乎没有人居住。
EN: The border town has become barren, with almost no inhabitants.

ZH: 这片荒芜的土地没有生长适合的作物。
EN: The barren land does not grow suitable crops.

ZH: 风吹过这片荒芜之地，掀起了一片尘土。
EN: The wind blew over the barren land, raising a cloud of dust.

ZH: 这座荒芜的废墟曾经是一座繁华的城市。
EN: This barren ruins used to be a thriving city.

ZH: 这片土地曾经丰饶，现在已经变得荒芜。
EN: This land used to be fertile, but now it has become barren.

ZH: 荒芜的地区需要大规模的恢复工程。
EN: The barren region needs large-scale restoration projects.

ZH: 过度开发导致这片河谷变得荒芜。
EN: Overdevelopment has caused this valley to become barren.

ZH: 没有及时的灌溉会让土地逐渐变得荒芜。
EN: Without timely irrigation, the land will gradually become barren.
